column_.text_: Sword of Eos, the Star Key
Sword of Eos, the Star Key
Knight of Ice, the Silver Blur
Golden Fists of Ura, No Mercy

This is a simple bronze sword that marks the beginning of a young boy's odyssey
into the endless blue—one which will lead him to the stars.

This dexterous saber can slice a boulder in half. It stole away in secret from
its master of old, presenting itself instead to a young hero.

Forged by Rolan, this sword emanates power from deep within.
Merely gripping its hilt fills one with boundless courage.

A hope-filled blade entrusted to  by Rolan, it holds the power
to dispel Angra Mainyu's dimension-warping gates. After tireless research,
its true might has been reawakened, ensuring that the will of a
sky-crossing shooting star lives on in the captain's grip.

This saber was inspired by the giant fish that the island peoples are so in awe
of. Yudhisthira islanders regard this strange-looking blade as a lucky charm.

The rocks cry for mercy, the skies tremble in fear, and the stars fall in
resignation at the very glint of this saber. Behold the ultimate sword.
Strike the gods, O wielder, and prevail.

The seven gems embedded in this giant blade represent the stars. While the
significance of that design has been lost to the ages, there is no doubting the
great power this sword possesses.

As the War hit its zenith, a weapon to silence the strife emerged. It had the 
power to destroy the world seven times over, a claim readily accepted by 
each new generation that heard the myth. Imprinted with its first owner's lust 
for power, it continues to roam battlefields in search of a worthy bearer.

This is a replica of a sword wielded by an Astral who attempted to destroy
the world. Its red blade represents the sky in flames; its loathsome hilt a
testament to undying hatred. One touch is enough to become tainted by its evil.
Seek to defy the inevitability of death before bearing the sword, skyfarer.

into the endless blue—one which will lead her to the stars.

This sword was given to a young girl on the day she vowed to become a chivalrous
knight. Since then, it has watched as months turned to years and a girl grew into
a guardian. Now it rests at her hip, ready to be drawn in defense of her
friends and allies.

The intense heat from this sword creates a shimmering haze in the air. Slip in
from the blind side of your distracted enemies, and cut them down.

Sincerity intensifies the deep blue radiance of this saber. Its ornamentation
makes any vow sworn on this blade as unbreakable as platinum.

A sword bequeathed to Katalina by her superior, it serves as a reminder of the
latter's failure, teaching the subordinate that protection, unlike destruction,
demands a tenacious spirit, unyielding and ever vigilant. And so the knight
whispers a prayer—that her charge's smile might persist another day.

A knight's honor shows in their unwavering loyalty and zealous devotion.
To uphold promise and dignity, the knight brandishes this ever-gleaming
sword, gambling her life every time she confronts injustice.

The light that shines off this silver rapier dances brilliantly yet fleetingly
in the air, not unlike the short-lived mayfly. With one well-placed thrust,
cruel as it is beautiful, its unfortunate target will be just as short-lived.

To hold a vow sacrosanct, an oath unbreakable, is to glimpse the face of
darkness. Consumed by vindictive desire, the knight wields this blade to protect
her liege, the last bastion of nobility in this forsaken sky.

For generations, Erste's kings bestowed this sword to the kingdom's protector.
Upon this blade each successive knight swore a solemn oath:
"I shan't ever waver in my duty. I shan't ever fail."
Only then did the blade grant power equal to the knight's resolve.

A young man made for piloting—a hope he'd once discarded, but could,
of course, never forget. And this gun, now an antique, watched over him all the
while. Yet however antiquated it may be, it won't let him down. It's seen
it all: his hopes, his dreams, and his failures.

This pistol has a sharp blade affixed to it, making it truly invaluable when
fighting in close quarters.

Blazing determination is what helps you stay your course against the buffeting
wind. Scorching wings guide bullets fired from this gun to the furthest horizon.

Slumbering for an eternity, this pistol landed in the hands of its current owner
from the ship's previous helmsman. To get the ship airborne once more—such a
promise was made to an irreplaceable friend. His unyielding commitment to
that promise roars through the azure blue with each shot fired.

Every now and then, a gentle breeze turns into a mighty gale and batters
humanity with terrible storms. But if one could only capture these rampant
zephyrs, and distill them into bullet form, skydwellers would possess a
mighty weapon indeed.

A long, long time ago there once was a hero who stood alone against countless
armies and fought them off with little more than a single gun. If rumors are
to be believed, the smoke from its muzzle rose into the sky to form a
battalion-smashing squall.

An evil gun spawned from the ancient dark arts. Only those who've signed a pact
with demons dare pull the trigger.

A bullet fired from this magic gun always hits its mark—even if that means 
bending the laws of time and space, circumventing trivial variables like 
distance, drag, and even cover. "One shot, one kill" doesn't get any more 
literal than that.

A little mage carried this staff as she pursued a hidden truth across the
scorched earth. So long as it was by her side, she even brought an iron
colossus to its knees, proof that she commanded magic which far outstripped
her peers.

Such is the power of this serpent-adorned staff that when held in reverent
supplication, it has been known to instantly cure affliction. Truly, it is a
miracle made manifest.

This staff is said to rob the powers of those who do evil and bring fortune to
those who do good. Whether it becomes boon or bane depends entirely upon the
quality of its wielder's heart.

Dwelling within this staff is the young girl's modest prayer to see her deceased
mother and father. In times of hardship, when her heart feels most frail, she
grips its familiar bough and remembers their faces.
She will bring out smiles in the sky—no matter what.

The design of this staff was inspired by an iron giant and is imbued with heat
as intense as hellfire. One flick unleashes enough destructive power
to melt down anything barring its way.

It is said that the fate of all things, down to every intricacy, is predestined
by the heavens. Only one power can rewrite that destiny: the will of people.
This miraculous staff amplifies one's will, transforming it into a means
to defy fate.

A divine staff used to achieve miracles. The intertwining twin snakes
make for wonderful guides who incessantly sing the praises of their wielder.

Many legends exist which tell of the feats performed by salvation's apostle—
the one who bore this staff. Afflictions cured, limbs restored, and even 
death's incursion reversed. Though it was often the spark of conflict, it is 
said only purehearted souls sanctioned by the gods may access its power.

The rifle of an old veteran who drowned his regret in the sea. Across the years
the weight of self-loathing wore him down, until he eventually became
unable to act. That is until a fateful encounter turned his loathing to resolve,
and he took up arms against the great evil consuming his homeland.

The soldier exhales, as if to keep the embers of a fire alive. They steady
their aim and wait for the order.

Camouflaged among rubble and debris, the invisible hunter strikes without
warning. Various attachments ensure that firepower doesn't come at the cost of
accuracy or range. No target who enters its crosshairs makes it home alive.

This rifle is a clumsy peace offering from a hurt daughter to a bungling father,
a small first step toward reconciliation. Repairing burnt bridges is never
easy, but the two continue to work at it, helped along by an invisible
cheerleader: the mother, who has never left their hearts or their thoughts.

This gun is imbued with the power of the primal beast Leviathan. Munitions
fired from its barrel overflow with torrential force.

Rustic in its aesthetics, ivory plating accentuates the barrel. Although this
firearm is particular in its chosen marksman, any competent gunner can
discharge the sound of victory upon the battlefield, deafening the ears of their
doomed foes.

The shape of this gun's barrel is reminiscent of Lindwurm's head. The trigger
is so heavy that an unworthy bearer would be unable to budge it, let alone
pull it. Flames surge forth from its draconic muzzle, not unlike the breath of
its namesake dragon, razing all in their path.

The will of the true dragon that dwells within this firearm manifests only 
before those it deems to be worthy. In its wish to bring tranquility to the 
skies, the dragon grants skyfarers the courage to defy fate and stand tall 
against even the coming apocalypse.

Deep within a forgotten forest, a beautiful maiden's dagger lies in wait for the
return of its wielder. Its fate was sealed when a crew of young skyfarers
invited the maiden to relive her glory days in the sky. Though a long-held
secret separates her from the crew, she's grateful to adventure once more.

According to rumor, this sword-snapping dagger was created by a bitter
blacksmith.

Roses adorn this dagger's exquisite blade, and its edge shimmers with a
mysterious sheen. It's as if it were forged in a time before time and served
in a world long lost to the skies.

There once was a young man who fell in a battle centuries ago, and he passed
his dagger—along with the sentiments it harbored—to Rose Queen. The true meaning
of the gesture escaped her until the present day, when she realized that
this was the first instance of unconditional love she'd received in the skies.

A dagger formed from the essence of a rose that blooms in flames. While its
exquisite appearance is quite alluring, its beauty belies the true nature of
its fanglike thorn.

A dagger which consumes even the most honorable men, it awoke in a burst of
blue flame when a knight gripped its hilt. The knight, staring into the depths
of the blaze, was terrified to see the most corrupt version of himself staring back.
It was only then that the once noble man knew he had fallen to darkness.

This dagger was created out of admiration for the powerful fangs of the great
dragon. A single strike can foretell the end of its victim as it rips through
the very fabric of fate, leaving no trace that the victim ever existed.

Forged by one devoted to the dragon of creation, this dagger's powers grow 
alongside the skill of its wielder—a weapon fit for heroes seeking to make 
history. For what better recourse is there when doom encircles the realm 
than an almighty manifestation of destruction?

This revenant whip in hand, a young woman prays for an everlasting
connection with those she crosses paths with. It pays heed to the screams
of lost souls and herds them to a more peaceful place.

A timeless classic for the man who lives and breathes street fashion. Buck all
the trends with the ultimate in functional accessories.

The powerful magic bubbling within this ethereal whip allows it to take on
countless forms. Chase not after its shadow, for its greenish-blue lashes seal
everything they touch, leaving only eternal ruin in their dreamlike wake.

When the vestige of her lost sister resurfaced from the sea of oblivion, the
bittersweet reunion dredged up tearful memories. Her sister beckoned; they'd
exit the cycle of death and rebirth together. But it was too good to be true.
The ghost girl belonged in the Sky Realm, with all its sorrows and joys.

Made of high-quality fire-resistant material, this whip can withstand any
flame for hours on end. Some have even used the whip as a torch, becoming 
bewitched by the dancing flames curling into the darkness.

A strike from this whip inflicts an unusual sense of tranquility. But this peace
is no more than an illusion of the mind, a defense mechanism drowning out the
horrors of inevitable agony.

There are worse things than death: like persisting as a lonesome specter for
so long that you forget your own name. She dreamt of her departed family every
night but had long since wept her tears dry. When she took up the whip, it was
like a second chance to save her loved ones, and in doing so, save herself.

As the ghostly girl stood before the tombstone, it finally sank in. Her sister,
her dear sister whom she'd been waiting for all these years, was never coming
back. It was time for the death-defying spirit to find a new purpose in these
skies. With her trusty whip in hand, she vowed to take hold of her own future.

Twin blades forged by an aloof blacksmith who retired to the forests of
Feendrache. Spurred by the fervent wish of an aspiring young man, he spent
seven days and seven nights pounding away on the glowing metal by his furnace.
One blade is imbued with the awe of a dragon; the other, the valor of a knight.

Drawing this frigid blade completely changes the atmosphere of battle.
It freezes anything it slices through, then shatters it like thin ice.

The incandescent flames of sorcery, the roaring blast of bombs, the fever pitch
of combatants, the spark of guns firing... This blade of ice swallows up
all such heat, bringing to the battlefield unprecedented snowfall.

The most powerful weapon on the field of battle is tenacity itself. Swords may
break, but so long as one's fighting spirit remains true, there remains a path
to victory.

Standing before the door of cataclysm, the knight's righteous sense of justice
bubbles forth from his heart. This stream of formidable power coalesces into
beautiful twinfang blades. Though they shine as bright as the soul of their
wielder, will it be enough to help dispel the looming darkness?

Devotion doesn't call for blind faith; a knight must watch their lord's every
step. When he sees his liege veer down the road of wickedness, he becomes a 
guidepost leading back to the path of righteousness. Though this attitude may
seem insubordinate, whole civilizations are steered by the king's sword.

The ultimate blade, forged in secret by the ancients. This indestructible knife
was created using a mysterious smelting technique that was lost with the decline
of their civilization.

Legend has it that these twin knives belonged to a chivalrous thief who saved 
many a rupieless victim from starvation. Although those souls are now 
lost to time, their gratitude lives on in the blades, blessing them to bring 
vast wealth to the wielder.

For one aspiring youth, the halberd was the obvious weapon of choice. This
one isn't the fastest or sharpest around, but wielded correctly, it's nigh
unbreakable. But for him it's not about being the greatest. It's about fighting
with friends on the front lines and letting them know they'll never be alone.

A massive war axe with a razor-sharp silver edge. A single lateral sweep
cuts through scores of soldiers in short order, while an overhead swing
can chop a person in twain like a piece of firewood.

A soldier needn't fear death while his allies cover his back. Nay, this show of
brotherhood should embolden him, give him the strength he needs to swing his
axe and ensure victory for his kingdom. Aye, if there's a weapon greater than a
true friend, I'd like to see it.

The young warrior, who'd dreamed of becoming a hero, had finally proven
himself after dozens of hard-fought victories. And through it all, he wielded
his trusty axe; a once uncelebrated weapon now made legendary.

The blade of this axe is made from a mysterious stone. It crackles with
lightning when swung, destroying monsters in the blink of an eye.

A breathtaking war axe that gives off the scent of beautiful flowers.
Even the most barbaric warriors will feel their bloodlust scatter away like
petals in the wind, removing death's stench from the battlefield, only
to repaint it with a spray of red.

A massive golden hammer that contains the power of thunder. No matter what
monster it faces, one strike from it rends its foe into the tiniest of pieces.

As time flowed on, the laws of nature could no longer contain the crackling
power of the magnificent hammer. Its crackling electricity evolved to atomize
everything it touched. One can't help but wonder if such shocking energy could
disintegrate the Omnipotent itself.

A prosperous kingdom devoid of war, tyranny, and betrayal—such a world
does this young man envision. His sword flickering like a flame in the wind,
our hero advances, ever closer to the world of his dreams.

This naked blade tinged with crimson serves all of creation, singing the elegies
of great heroes. It has the power to bend fate to its will, burning away the
buds of future calamity.

A sword with ancient origins, this blade has been passed down for generations as
a family heirloom. It's said that this sword was favored by a great nobleman who
had the weapon engraved with images of the stunning vistas witnessed on his
summer excursions.

This saber delights in victory, changing color depending on its master.
It takes but a command, and all you desire will be yours.

An ideal king and an ideal subject are one and the same. Both would humbly
serve not out of self-interest but rather their people—their country. They are
rich in heart, rising to meet whatever challenge they should face. Waver not
does the fiercest fire; stray not does the steadfast countryman.

Blazing sword in hand, our hero illuminates the world as a bonfire does a dark
night. Ready to cut open a path toward his ideals, he will not leave even one
citizen unhappy. Naive though he may be, the man holds fast to his beliefs.
This weapon coupled with his strength will achieve his goal.

Reflected within this silver brand's lazuline inlay is its wielder, the one who
will rule over all. Seeking a world of peace, he unsheathes his weapon—a
blade shimmering brightly with crystals of ice destined to change fate itself.

To walk the path of a ruler is to see how war shatters the hearts and minds 
of the innocent. A king without power is doomed to see all they cherish slip 
through their fingers. Lives cannot be saved by compassion alone—only the 
honed prowess of an ever-loyal sword can guide a people to prosperity.

Embroiled in bitter conspiracy more times than our hero can count, he no 
longer finds meaning in both honor and dishonor alike. What remains is an
enduring vow of eternal loyalty to his country and his former king.
Donning his black armor, sword in hand, he mourns over a bygone era.

Wielding this massive sword requires the strength of primal beast Titan himself.
Its blade bears countless scars as proof of the numerous times its master
has thwarted death.

King of sabers, this winged symbol of calamity has destroyed countless lives.
One arc of its blade can strike anything in the great blue sky with terrifying
accuracy. Its victims don't have so much as a chance to fight back before
they are hurled into oblivion.

The unyielding saber of legend that felled True Dragon Fafnir. Natural talent
and daily training coalesced into one—and together with the odious power
of dragons—our hero accomplished many a deed. Yet he has no interest in radiant
past glories. He wishes only for peace throughout his beloved homeland.

This blade has drunk from so many veins, it's turned jet black. Yet oddly enough,
the more it cuts, the sharper it gets.

A beautiful sword with an elegant curve often mistaken for a work of art.
But to handle this weapon carelessly is a grave mistake. For a soul that is not
prepared to use this blade will incur its wrath and return to ash.

This blade shimmers like a bright blue flame. One searing stroke from this saber
melts everything in its path.

Let none mistake the burning spirit of the one who tempered and honed this 
celebrated blade. Primal beast power swirls within the inlaid jewel upon its 
hilt, granting it the strength to cleave iron, sunstone, and even dimensions—
depending on who you ask.

The blade of this divine saber was forged using a rare translucent crystal that
glistens with resplendent shades of aquamarine. Such a sublime creation
permits only the most holy and fully realized of knights to wield its power
in order to assure indomitable valor and the greatest of glory.

The essence of a perfect sword lies not in its blade but rather in the
unwavering confidence and determination of its wielder. A true warrior
forges one's mind and sharpens one's senses through the fires of training.

How deep a wound can this blade carve, you ask? What a ridiculous question. 
To those confused about the weapon's purpose, I shall impart upon you this:
secure victory not by a slicing cut but rather a crushing blow.

When once asked, "Does your violence serve a just cause?" she then
replied, "Violence is nothing more than strength in the absence of
justice." There is no room for hesitation on the path of the righteous,
for the sword mirrors the heart.

Red as the flames of passion, this blade was tempered with memories of ancient
sin. It can set its wielder's soul ablaze with fury and reduce all of creation
to ash in a single swing.

This blade glows with the desire to exterminate evil. Villainy shan't be
permitted to thrive. All deeds will be measured by the scale, and one's
true intentions—vice or virtue—shall be put to the test.

Its narrow hilt, combined with a conversely bulky blade, enables a swing of
dizzying force. While even a novice could wreak considerable destruction with
this marvel, in the hands of a master, there exists not a single entity it would
fail to cleave.

As the hero raises a triumphant shout, the blade glows with both the 
exultations of the victor and the grudge of the defeated. Yet it is at the peak 
of battle that the sword truly shines; only at the precipice of death will the 
warrior be enveloped by the sword's serene, calming light.

The codger planned to spend his final years fishing, but all he sees now are
promising youths, lost and floundering. He lays down his rod for the sword and
sails to their aid. His future may be short, but society grows when the old
plant trees under whose shade they will never sit.

This blade burns with a bottomless anger as hot as lava. Its boiling rage
will not cool until everything has been reduced to embers.

It gleams a lustrous scarlet, almost as if it were made of precious gemstone.
It is a symbol of a warrior's strength, and whoever bears it is recognized
as a world-famous blademaster.

When this renowned blade came into the fabled warrior's possession, it soon
grew dull from making scofflaws repent and blood-crazed beasts whimper. As
it remained sheathed and too blunt to cut, that signaled that true peace had
arrived. He once had a hundred disciples, but that's all in the past now.

Legend has it that the gloaming opens a door to another world. It's the
golden hour when cicadas raise their shrill choirs, singing to a forgotten land.
That is why this sword is named for the evening cicada. Like the insect's
fleeting life span, so too is a foe's existence when facing down this edge.

The skies tremble upon hearing its name. The scars this blade inflicts yield to
no potion or healing touch. To escape the ceaseless torment, there is
but one hope: death.

Those who live and breathe swordplay have heard the tale of the slender, silver-
bellied swordfish at least once. It resembles tempered steel, and according to
legend, someone once cut through solid rock with it. The stunt earned them a
reputation as a master swordsman, though it was only done to draw a few laughs.

This wisened fisherman dedicated every fiber of his being to honing the 
sharpness of blade, wit, and hook. At the end of years of angling, he let out a 
mighty whoop. An azure fish that shatters the earth, that cloaks the sky in 
debris—a fish now his. Or so the story goes.

During her adolescent years, this rising warrior wished to emulate the swordsman
she revered by swinging this ungainly blade as easily as he did. It took months
of brutal training to master its heft, but now each of her swings leaves behind
a beautiful lavender arc as if to symbolize a butterfly taking flight.

Many warriors desire this katana for its graceful form. Enemies fall before it
in the blink of an eye. Flame erupts from the blade upon impact, inflicting
burning wounds that will never heal.

This legendary katana will only allow itself to be wielded by a ruler who
heeds the troubles of people great and small. Its benevolence clears the world
of chaos and carves a path toward peace.

A noble blade fit for one who seeks to reach the pinnacle of swordplay, it
rises to its greatest heights in the hands of the unyielding swordswoman.
She channels her unshakeable focus into the katana to shatter the stars with
supremely honed strikes. And yet, the approval she wants still eludes her.

This katana gives off a clear blue aura. No matter how many enemies it cuts
through, it never grows sullied. If this beautiful blade should ever chip or
otherwise be damaged, do not despair. It will be remade overnight, as sharp
and lethal as ever.

A blade reserved solely for waterfall training on a wintry holiday. Those
who complete the arduous trial are freed of all impure thoughts, allowing them
to take in the beauty of the holy eve in all its glory.

With one gleaming swing this blade causes mountains to crash down, splattering
red earth onto the riverbanks like blood.

The katana that toppled eight summits, its edge has become so sharp that it
can cut air itself. With a sweep of the blade, magma pours from the open wound
carved out of the mountainside. Truly, this is a weapon of cataclysmic repute.

This gauntlet blossoms like a lotus flower with the collective heat of
the passion that burns within all living creatures. Its blazing petals dance
through the heavens and devour the old world to make way for the new.

Most would say that the ascetic ways venture into madness by denying the
pleasures of life. But those who follow the purest path and cast away such
aspersions—along with any notions of pride, arrogance, and scorn—would do
well to train with this austere armament.

Long ago, an evil demon was sealed away and destroyed deep in a caldera. This
gauntlet rose out of the magma boiling up from that very spot, burning with
destructive desire.

According to biomechanics, the most powerful punch one can throw is the straight
punch, which concentrates the greatest speed and mass into the smallest possible
point. These golden gloves were crafted around that theory, and when worn by
a master pugilist, place demonic destruction in the fists of a mortal.

Throwing fists of demonic force, he tears open the skies and upends mountains.
To the foes that lie before his feet, defeated by his supreme punches, he shows
gratitude with thunderous claps that echo for miles. Anyone who embarks on a
path to break their limits follows in the ways of the Eternal Rage Style.

This gauntlet of hardened plates seems to shimmer with hidden knowledge. And
upon being worn by a worthy pugilist, its secrets are revealed, transforming it
into a weapon of ascetic destruction. Hapless enemies are left in ruin with their
souls snuffed out for eternity.

A legendary hero’s beloved weapon. Even battle-hardened warriors dare not
steal it, lest they face the godlike wrath that still lies within.

An undefeated champion once said he was never cornered in battle, despite an
incident in which a legion cut off his retreat and encircled him in a ring of
fire. The path forward was clear; he needed only to punch a hole in the ground,
a daring feat made effortless by the godly gauntlet that bolstered his fist.

Restricted file—code name: Arvess. A cross-tipped spear of lunar origin.
This seal weapon harnesses the power of flames. While Arvess augments its
contractor's agility, it has a tendency to over-amplify the wielder's natural
arrogance. Great care must be taken in choosing Arvess's contractor.

Its blade burns with a dark, sweltering flame. The sphere resting at its center
blazes hot and black like a sunspot. This fiery spear represents the fullest
realization of searing sorcery, turning swaths of foes to ash in an instant.

One thrust from this spear is destructive enough to pierce through every
living thing in the sky; any who dares bar its path meets a quick, crushing end.
Its everlasting light promises victory without fail.

Day in, day out, the freewheeling gladiator charges at whatever enemy or 
predicament life chooses to throw her way. After all, why live as a doormat? 
She'd rather hurtle across the battlefield, skewering and roasting her foes.

This spear has passed through the hands of many who seek revenge.
Silently, it grants them power to match their hatred, ensuring that their
vengeance is carried out.

Central pillar of the four beasts, this golden spear was forged with scales
from Huanglong. Heavenly aid comes in the form of divine radiance,
piercing through darkened skies. One could say it's the crowning
achievement of all creation.

A mythical spear bestowed from the Queen of Shadow. Formed by sharpening
the bone of a sea dragon, it slaughtered enemies in a single thrust,
reducing the duress faced by ancient heroes.

The remains of a sea dragon that challenged the god of the sea—and lost—festered
for years on end. Then the children of man shaped its bones into a spear
brimming with defiance to the gods. The rebellious weapon is said to harbor
the power to drown despair and divert destiny's flow.

Restricted file—code name: Grynoth. A massive scythe of lunar origin.
This seal weapon harnesses ethereal darkness. While Grynoth augments its
contractor's endurance, it has a tendency to over-amplify the wielder's
animosity. Great care must be taken in choosing Grynoth's contractor.

A massive scythe forged by a purehearted blacksmith for the one she
cares most about. The fleeting tears she sheds in worry of the lucky man
may very well prove to be more empowering than any weapon in this world.
A time to sow, a soul to reap. A time to live, a time to weep.

He escaped from that fateful battle with nothing but his altered body, his
scythe, and an undying regret for failing to save his comrades. To this day, he
risks his life on the front line, for in his mind, no other way exists to give
his soul meaning. He will never lose another friend again.

The crescent moon grows murkier for each soul it devours.
The weight of so many lives may eventually send it plunging into the abyss,
yet the bewitchingly fine edge is always searching for its next victim.

The scythe of order that governs chaos. Created from the power of dragons
by their red-eyed master, its crystalline form contains prayers of cerulean.
Its radiance gives way to dawn, instilling order in a troubled world.

One blow from this perilous scythe banishes its victim's soul straight
to the underworld. Once damned, a spirit is doomed to wander in
chaotic darkness for eternity.

A moldered pot in the underworld stews with souls reaped by this scythe. They
congeal at the bottom into grotesque beings, and their ghastly wails of acrimony
permeate from the scythe's edge. This is their gateway back to the living world,
and they demand more sacrifices.

A tome filled with the bountiful knowledge of the founder of alchemy. Though its
pages hold the profane secret of eternal life, modern scholars have determined
it must be no more than a treatise on esoteric philosophy. After all, whole
reams of its contents are devoted to "the Glorious Pursuit of Cuteness."

Possessing the power to influence dreams, dream weavers never leave home
without it. Caution: Dreams are a vital but fragile link between body and mind.
Improper use of the Dream Atlas may result in falling into an eternal
dream-like state.

Both beginning and end, all and nothing. Infinity is like a Möbius strip: not
two-sided, but forming an endless circle. Therein lies eternal truth beyond
mortal knowledge; for man is finite and will never touch infinity. Only those
who eat their own tail can escape, albeit at the cost of exile from paradise.

Not a soul has ever finished this book, for none can withstand the sheer volume
of its endless taboos and wisdoms. An ordinary person would see information
beyond comprehension flood their mind at once, be consumed by a lethal number
of intersecting theories and calculations, and be functionally immobilized.

This volume collects a number of potent incantations and forbidden spells.
Unless one has spent a significant amount of time dabbling in the supernatural,
merely touching this tome is highly discouraged.

A book with a spectacular primal beast adorning its cover. The creature was said
to have the ability to transform reality into written record. Thus the many
tragedies it delivered unto the Sky Realm incidentally became immortalized in
history.

a rapacious pioneer who stretched the frontiers of mortal knowledge. He favored
intricate parables and allegories; to unravel even one of his truths takes
centuries. Small wonder, then, that much of this tome is still undeciphered.

Curiosity? It's our greatest gift. But the weak flame we light to illuminate our
ignorance is easily snuffed by the whisper of doubt from our souls. Humanity
shall burn itself out of existence, yet still demand wisdom as smoldering ash.
In front of the final door, we must transcend the self. —Zosimos's Last Musings
